Subject: Re: [T2] adj hyd valves at 0 or 7.5 btdc? please clarify

On Wednesday, September 22, 2004, at 02:52PM, KYLE LAFERRIERE <klaferriere(-at-)msn.com> wrote:

>thanks everyone who answered my question about adjusting hydralic valves.
>A couple of you said to line up the mark on the fan with 0 (with the rotor 
>at the #1 cylinder).
>Then turn 180 degrees (rotor turns 90) counterclockwise.
>Why do I line up the mark with 0 instead of 7.5 since thats what I set my 
>timing to.

Because you want the valve to be closed.

>Also, is it important for my timing to be perfect before I do 
>this?

No, valves are adjusted before doing the timing.

